net.sf.jclec.mo.indicator

Class RelativeProgress

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.indicator.Indicator
      • net.sf.jclec.mo.indicator.TernaryIndicator
        • net.sf.jclec.mo.indicator.RelativeProgress
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC

    public class RelativeProgress
extends TernaryIndicator
    The Progress indicator measures the relative convergence improvement in terms of generational distance. It requires two pareto fronts, one representing the set of solutions at the first generation and the other containing the set of solution at a generic generation, t. The convergence is measured in terms of the achieved generational distance (GD).

    Book: C.A. Coello Coello, D.A. Van Veldhuizen, G.B. Lamont. "Evolutionary Algorithms for Solving Multi-Objective Problems". 1st edition. Kluwer Academic Publ. 2002.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Aurora Ramirez (AR), Jose Raul Romero (JRR), Sebastian Ventura (SV)

    Knowledge Discovery and Intelligent Systems (KDIS) Research Group: http://www.uco.es/grupos/kdis

    See Also:
